Does $\blueD{(9 \times 2) \times 5}=\purpleC{9 \times 10}?$

$
\begin{align}
\blueD{(9 \times 2) \times 5} &\stackrel{?}{=}  \purpleC{9 \times 10}
\\\\
\blueD{9 \times (2 \times 5)} &\stackrel{?}{=}  \purpleC{9 \times 10} &&\text{Associative property of multiplication}\\\\
\blueD{9 \times 10} &=  \purpleC{9 \times 10}
 \end{align}$

Yes, $\blueD{(9 \times 2) \times 5}$ is equivalent to $\purpleC{9 \times 10}$.
